"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457475","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-08","<p>The information requested is obtainable from a discussion document on IR35 published by HM Revenue and Customs on 17 July which is available at the following link :</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/446242/Intermediaries_legislation_IR35-discussion_document.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/446242/Intermediaries_legislation_IR35-discussion_document.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-03-08T14:34:57.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457475/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457475/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457475/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-03","Self-employed: Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of how many personal service companies are in operation in the UK.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457476","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-08","<p>The government will consult on the detail of the new reforms in due course. The consultation will be accompanied by an impact assessment.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2016-03-08T17:03:43.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457476/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457476/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457476/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-03","Personal Injury","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the effect on court fee income of changes to personal injury law and procedure prior to making his announcement in the 2015 Autumn Statement; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","29782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457477","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-08","<p>The Ministry of Justice will launch a public consultation in due course on the details of the policy. This will be accompanied by an impact assessment.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-03-08T14:38:44.15Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457477/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457477/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457477/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-03","Personal Injury","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect on income tax receipts of changes to personal injury law and procedure prior to making his announcement in the 2015 Autumn Statement; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","29783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457478","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-08","<p>The proportion of the Department’s invoices for goods and services supplied by private companies and small and medium-sized enterprises cannot be reliably extrapolated from our current payment system as it doesn’t link or split payment performance in this way.</p><p>As of the last quarter, the Department paid 89% of invoices within 5 days. The Department’s prompt payment data can be accessed via this link: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dclg-and-pins-prompt-payment-data-2015</p><p> </p><p>Of the Department’s current contracts, 33% are held by small and medium-sized enterprises. The Department’s annual spend on these as a proportion of our overall spend with suppliers is 25.4%.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-08T17:20:58.207Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457478/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457478/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457478/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-03","Department for Communities and Local Government: Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of his Department's invoices for goods and services supplied by (a) private companies and (b) small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) are completed on time; and what proportion of the (i) number and (ii) value of contracts between his Department and private companies are held by SMEs.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","29667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457479","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-11","<p><br>The numbers of dwellings completed by houisng associations and local authorities in England between 1997 and 2015 were as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Housing associations</p></td><td><p>Local authorities</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1997</p></td><td><p>20,970</p></td><td><p>290</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1998</p></td><td><p>19,900</p></td><td><p>240</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1999</p></td><td><p>17,780</p></td><td><p>50</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2000</p></td><td><p>16.680</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2001</p></td><td><p>14,500</p></td><td><p>160</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2002</p></td><td><p>13,310</p></td><td><p>180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2003</p></td><td><p>12,820</p></td><td><p>180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2004</p></td><td><p>16.600</p></td><td><p>130</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005</p></td><td><p>17,540</p></td><td><p>180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006</p></td><td><p>20,660</p></td><td><p>280</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>22,180</p></td><td><p>250</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>26,470</p></td><td><p>430</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>26,990</p></td><td><p>360</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>22,650</p></td><td><p>790</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>25,940</p></td><td><p>2,230</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>25,440</p></td><td><p>1,410</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>21,590</p></td><td><p>840</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>23,780</p></td><td><p>1,180</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>30,200</p></td><td><p>1,640</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Statistics on new build housing starts and completions in England, and in each local authority district, are published on the Department's website at:</p><p>http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-house-building</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-11T14:16:57.063Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457479/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457479/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457479/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-03","Social Rented Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many Government-sponsored new social and council houses were built between (a) 1997 and 2010 and (b) 2010 and 2016.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457480","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-11","<p>The Department has to date not received any applications for a Lancashire Combined Authority. To make such an application an area must, in accordance with the provisoins of the Local Democracy, Economic Development and Construction Act 1999, as amended by the Cities and Local Government Devolution Act 2016, undertake a gvoernance review for the area and also publish a scheme setting out propsals for a Combined Authority. They must also undertake a public consultation on these proposals and provide a summary of these proposals to the Secretary of State.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-03-11T13:39:01.9Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457480/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457480/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457480/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-03","Combined Authorities: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the application for a Lancashire combined authority; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457481","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-10","<p>The Department does not collect information on the number of planning applications by parliamentary constituency.</p><p>However it collects the numbers of decisions made at a local planning authority level. In the six months to 31 December 2015 Lancaster City Council, within which the hon, Member's constituency falls, has made decisions on applications for:</p><p>- 18 major residential developments</p><p>- 27 minor residential developments</p><p>- Permitted development rights for one ‘office to residential’ scheme and nine ‘agricultural to residential’ schemes</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-10T16:19:34.823Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457481/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457481/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457481/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-03","Housing: Morecambe and Lunesdale","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many planning applications for new homes or conversions of existing buildings have been made in Morecambe and Lunesdale constituency since June 2015.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457482","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Chatsworth Gardens project, known as West End One, is a flagship private rent project involving refurbishing and remodelling 27 empty properties to create 51 (1, 2, 3, &amp; 4-bed) homes. Work on site commenced in early 2015 and, to date, ten 4-bedroom houses have been completed. The project is supported by £8.3 million of funding from the Homes and Communities Agency and £1.9 million of empty homes funding.</p><p>The next release of new homes is expected later this month, with completion of all units by Autumn 2016. West End Two, the adjacent site is to follow on directly creating a further 50 homes for private rent.</p><p>The Department does not collect data on all housing developments across the country, but 13 developments, either completed since 2014 or are currently on site, across the Lancaster City Council area have received Social Housing Grant via the Homes and Communities Agency, totalling £8.0 million and are providing a total of 231 new affordable homes.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-14T16:43:03.083Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457482/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457482/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457482/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-03","Housing: Morecambe and Lunesdale","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether he has been notified of any funding applications from Lancaster City Council for the West End of Morecambe; and what information his Department holds on progress being made on (a) the Chatsworth Gardens project and (b) any other new housing projects in Morecambe and Lunesdale constituency.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457483","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-09","<p>My rt hon. Friend, the Chancellor announced the Lancashire Local Enterprise Partnership’s successful bid for a new Enterprise Zone at Hillhouse as part of the 2015 Autumn Statement. This followed approval of the business case for the Blackpool Enterprise Zone which was announced on 12 November 2015.</p><p>Regulations are being laid for both Enterprise Zones to enable them to offer business rate discounts and enhanced capital allowances from April 2016. The new Enterprise Zones complement the existing Lancashire Local Enterprise Zone which covers sites at Warton and Samlesbury.</p><p> </p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-03-09T17:03:42.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457483/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457483/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457483/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-03","Enterprise Zones: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what progress his Department is making on the Enterprise Zones applied for by the Lancashire Enterprise Partnership; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457484","Department for Transport","false","2016-03-11","<p>Progress in respect to the repairs to the Loyn Bridge following damage caused by the winter storms is entirely a matter for Lancashire County Council as local highway authority. The Department for Transport ‎has provided £5 million funding to the Council and they will undertake repairs to the bridge as soon as practicable.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-03-11T11:31:48.87Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457484/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457484/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457484/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-03-03","Bridges: Gressingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on the progress of repairs to the Loyn Bridge in Gressingham in the Lune Valley in Morecambe and Lunesdale constituency.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457485","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-08","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my previous answer to him on 29 February, PQ 28338. The £140 million loan fund was determined as part of the Spending Review. The new fund will be used to lever in private sector funding to enable estate regeneration, and will be able to be drawn down alongside other supportive Government programmes. Under the right conditions some schemes could be self-financing.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-03-08T16:44:30.613Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457485/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457485/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457485/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-03","Housing Estates: Regeneration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the Prime Minister's announcement of 10 January 2016, Prime Minister pledges to transform sink estates, how the figure of £140 million relating to the redevelopment of 100 sink estates was calculated.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","29619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457486","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-11","<p>The Government has made it clear that the variation in estimated revenue generated by the adult social care precept, which is one source of funding for adult social care will be taken into account when publishing the proposed allocations for the additional Better Care Fund funding (£1.5 billion by 2019-20).</p><p>The proposed allocations will be subject to a public consultation later this year.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-03-11T13:40:12.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457486/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457486/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457486/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-03","Social Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of variations in revenue generated by the social care precept on levels of variation in the standard of social care across the UK.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","29635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457487","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-08","<p>DCLG published a plain English guide to open and accountable local government in August 2014. Ultimately it is for local decision makers to decide what information should be recorded and publicly available on the basis of the national rules and for local electors to hold them to account for this.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-03-08T16:42:37.3Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457487/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457487/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457487/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-03","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of guidance issued to councils on budget transparency.","false","Biography information for Mims Davies","Eastleigh","Mims Davies","29624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457488","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-08","<p>The Heritage Lottery Fund is able to support projects concerned with historic battlefield landscapes. Over the coming months the Heritage Minister will be visiting several battlefield sites both at home and abroad to commemorate important events such as the Battle of Hastings and to promote battlefield tourism. The Battlefields Trust is on hand to help preserve and promote battlefield heritage across the UK and local authorities may also be able to help promote battlefields.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-08T15:01:21.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457488/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457488/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457488/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Tourism: Battles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans he has to promote battlefield tourism in England in the next 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","29610"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457489","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-09","<p>The Government published the Evaluation of Gaming Machine (Circumstances of Use) (Amendment) Regulations 2015 on 21 January. The Evaluation can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-gaming-machine-circumstances-of-useamendment-regulations-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-gaming-machine-circumstances-of-useamendment-regulations-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>The evaluation indicates that a large proportion of players of FOBTs may now be making a more conscious choice to control their playing behaviour and their stake level. We will now consider the findings of the evaluation before deciding if there is a need for further action.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-09T09:41:47.443Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457489/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457489/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457489/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Gaming Machine (Circumstances of Use) (Amendment) Regulations 2015","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Gaming Machine Regulations 2015; and if he will take further steps to limit the stake on fixed odds betting terminals.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","29636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457490","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-08","<p>Registered battlefields are protected through the planning system under the terms of the National Planning Policy Framework. Historic England maintains the register of historic battlefields on the National Heritage List for England.</p><p> </p><p>I am pleased to say the Heritage Lottery Fund are able to support projects concerned with protecting and promoting large landscapes such as a battlefield site. Funding may also be available from the relevant local authority.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-08T16:50:54.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457490/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457490/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457490/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Cultural Heritage: Battles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what (a) protection and (b) funding is available for historic battlefields in (i) England and (ii) Northam in Torridge and West Devon constituency.","false","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","29599"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457491","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-08","<p>The Prime Minister’s Five Point Plan for Tourism sets out the Government’s commitment to encourage tourists to explore beyond London.</p><p> </p><p>According to the Office for National Statistics International Passenger Survey, there were 1.9 million inbound visits to the south west of England in the first nine months of 2015 (Jan-Sep); up 6% compared to the same period in 2014. Overseas visitors spent £0.84 billion during these visits, up 2% on Jan-Sep 2014. The £5 million South West Tourism Growth Fund, announced last year, will further promote tourism in the South-West of England.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-08T16:38:41.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457491/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457491/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457491/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Tourism: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he has taken to promote tourism in the south west of England in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","29601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457492","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-09","<p>The Government published the Evaluation of Gaming Machine (Circumstances of Use) (Amendment) Regulations 2015 on 21 January. The Evaluation can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-gaming-machine-circumstances-of-useamendment-regulations-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-gaming-machine-circumstances-of-useamendment-regulations-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>The evaluation indicates that a large proportion of players of FOBTs may now be making a more conscious choice to control their playing behaviour and their stake level. We will now consider the findings of the evaluation before deciding if there is a need for further action.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-09T09:45:42.233Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457492/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457492/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457492/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on gambling addiction of limiting the stake on fixed odds betting terminals; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","29602"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457493","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-09","<p>Prior to the consultation opening, no estimate was made of the number of expected responses. Over 192,000 responses were received, with over 140,000 responses submitted in the final 2 weeks of the 12 week consultation period.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-09T10:59:10.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457493/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457493/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457493/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","BBC: Royal Charters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many responses he (a) expected to receive and (b) received to the consultation on BBC Charter Review.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","29589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457494","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-10","<p>The Theatres Trust administers the Theatres Protection Fund scheme, which provides funds to theatres in need and at risk. Theatres on the 'Heritage at Risk' Register are also able to apply for repair grants provided by Historic England.</p><p>In addition, the Heritage Lottery Fund may also be able to fund wider projects relating to theatres, which could cover restoration costs.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-10T12:27:11.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457494/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457494/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457494/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Theatres: Coastal Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what funds and funding streams are available to member trusts for restoration of theatres in coastal areas.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457495","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-08","<p>The World Anti-Doping Agency, to which the UK pays an annual fee, conducts research into anti-doping in sport that is utilised by national anti-doping organisations including UK Anti-Doping.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-08T09:24:46.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457495/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457495/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457495/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Sports: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether he has had discussions with (a) Cabinet colleagues and (b) sporting stakeholders on setting up an independent body to fund research into anti-doping in sport; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","29680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457496","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-08","<p>UK Anti-Doping is an Arms Length Body of DCMS and regularly advises my Department on all anti-doping matters.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-08T09:21:37.043Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457496/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457496/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457496/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Sports: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what information his Department holds into anti-doping in UK sport; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","29679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457497","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-10","<p>Morecambe and Lunesdale has enjoyed record levels of funding over the past three years - £105,182 in 2013/14; £164,390 in 2014/15; and £321,295 in 2015/16 (year to date to 7th March).</p><p><br>This investment from Arts Council England has supported a number of exciting projects, including Lancaster Arts Partnership First Fridays, the Mirrored Minds Research and Development project.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-10T16:55:11.863Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457497/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457497/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457497/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Arts: Morecambe and Lunesdale","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much funding his Department has allowed to arts groups in the Morecambe and Lunesdale constituency in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457498","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-08","<p>UK Anti-Doping’s dedicated Science and Medical team work closely with the Drug Control Centre at King’s College London and others to research new substances and methods of using performance enhancing substances, as well as provide expertise in helping to develop new detection methods.</p><p> </p><p>Under the World Anti-Doping Code, UK Anti-Doping can store samples for up to 10 years to allow retrospective testing of samples as new testing methods are developed.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-08T09:29:12.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457498/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457498/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457498/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-03-03","Sports: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to ensure that bodies undertaking anti-doping investigations in UK sport have access to the most up-to-date science and technology; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","29678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457499","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-10","<p>The Secretary of State discussed these issues with the Chamber of Commerce and local businesses when he visited the Falkland Islands in February. British Forces South Atlantic Islands (BFSAI) will continue to work with the local commercial sector, including the Falkland Islands Chamber of Commerce, to develop opportunities for local supply of good and services including by small and medium-sized enterprises, within the legal and regulatory constraints that govern the Ministry of Defence's commercial activity. For example, we have recently put in place arrangements for the supply of locally generated renewable energy to BFSAI and to employ local companies for infrastructure work.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-03-10T16:08:01.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457499/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457499/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457499/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-03","Falkland Islands: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps are being taken to improve the mutual supply chain of goods and services between the Mount Pleasant Military Base and small and medium-sized enterprises and the Chamber of Commerce in the Falkland Islands.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","29712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457500","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-10","<p>Personnel in receipt of Excess Fares Allowance, Paid Car Allowance or Subsidised Health Insurance are employed in the Job Families outlined below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Business Management and Improvement</p></td><td><p>Estates</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Commercial</p></td><td><p>Finance</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Communications and Media</p></td><td><p>Health Professionals</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Corporate Support</p></td><td><p>Health, Safety and Environmental Protection</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Defence Equipment and Support (DE&amp;S) Commercial</p></td><td><p>Human Resources</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DE&amp;S Corporate Services</p></td><td><p>Information</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DE&amp;S Engineering</p></td><td><p>Internal Audit</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DE&amp;S Finance and Accounting</p></td><td><p>Logistics</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DE&amp;S Human Resources</p></td><td><p>Policy Strategy and Parliamentary</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DE&amp;S Information Management and IT</p></td><td><p>Portfolio, Programme and Project</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DE&amp;S Integrated Logistics</p></td><td><p>Security</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DE&amp;S Project Controls</p></td><td><p>Training and Education</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DE&amp;S Project Management</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Defence Intelligence</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Engineering and Science</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Notes:</p><p>Job Families are a broader grouping based upon the type of role.</p><p>Job Families where five or less personnel are in receipt of one or more allowances have not been included.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-03-10T16:07:34.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457500/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457500/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457500/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-03","Ministry of Defence: Fringe Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 22 February 2016 to Question 26813, what the job titles are of those people in receipt of excess fares allowance, paid car allowances or subsidised health insurance.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","29729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457501","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-08","<p>The Radiation (Emergency Preparedness and Public Information) Regulations 2001 apply to areas, defined in each case by the Office for Nuclear Regulation, surrounding nuclear sites. The regulations do not apply to road transport and therefore no guidance is issued.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-08T16:45:39.283Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457501/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457501/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457501/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-03","Nuclear Weapons: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what guidance is issued under the Radiation (Emergency Preparedness and Public Information) Regulations 2001 to homes along the route of convoys transporting nuclear weapons.","false","Biography information for Owen Thompson","Midlothian","Owen Thompson","29773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457502","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-08","<p>The Ministry of Defence's humanitarian relief deployments are typically in response to either a request from the Department for International Development or directly from the government affected. The UK did not receive a request for assistance from the Fijian government and so currently has no plans to deploy personnel or assets.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-08T16:46:14.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457502/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457502/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457502/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-03","Fiji: Storms","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he plans to deploy (a) Fijian soldiers serving in the British Army and (b) other Army resources for humanitarian purposes in Fiji in response to the recent cyclone.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","29646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457503","Department for Education","false","2016-03-11","<p>It is important that school staff have the training they need to equip them to identify children at risk of being drawn into terrorism and to challenge extremist ideas. Individual schools are best placed to assess their training needs in the light of their assessment of the risk. The Department’s core statutory safeguarding guidance Keeping Children Safe in Education makes clear that, as a minimum, designated safeguarding leads in schools and colleges should be trained in Prevent. This is available on GOV.UK at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/keeping-children-safe-in-education--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/keeping-children-safe-in-education--2</a></p><p> </p><p>To help raise awareness of Prevent and issues around radicalisation amongst front line staff, the Home Office is continuing to roll out freely available Workshops to Raise Awareness of Prevent (WRAP). There are a number of professionals, particularly in safeguarding roles, many of whom work within local authorities and the police, who are accredited WRAP facilitators. There has been a significant increase in the number of WRAP training sessions delivered since the end of 2014. The greatest volume of WRAP training has taken place in schools with a significant increase in numbers of staff trained. Over 32,000 staff within schools were WRAP trained in 2015. Home Office does not hold separate data on training in different types of schools or the frequency of Prevent training.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-03-11T11:57:00.693Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457503/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457503/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457503/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-03","Schools: Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many staff in state-funded schools have received Prevent awareness training.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","29632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457504","Department for Education","false","2016-03-11","<p>I refer the Honourable member to my response to question 29204 submitted to Parliament on Friday 4 March 2016. The answer shows that the total number of primary and secondary pupils in excess of capacity has reduced by 47,513 between 2010 and 2014.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-03-11T11:58:06.233Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457504/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457504/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457504/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-03","Schools: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Prime Minister's oral contribution of 2 March 2016, Official Report, column 943, what the evidential basis is for the statement that there are 36,500 fewer pupils in overcrowded schools than in 2010.","false","Biography information for Tristram Hunt","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Tristram Hunt","29633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457505","Department for Education","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Teachers’ Pensions Regulations currently provide for supply teachers to participate in the Teachers’ Pension Scheme (TPS) where they are employed by a scheme employer. These are local authorities (LAs), academies and further education colleges. This includes supply teachers who are recruited by a supply agency but then employed directly, under a contract of employment, by the scheme employer.</p><p> </p><p>Where supply teachers are self-employed or remain employed by a supply agency and their services are provided under a ‘contract for services’, it is not possible for them to participate in the TPS as there is no organisation to undertake the employer role, including remitting contributions to the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not plan to review these arrangements and considers that it is for employers and teachers to determine how supply teachers are employed, which can in turn enable access to the TPS under the current arrangements.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-03-14T16:05:47.487Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457505/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457505/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457505/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-03","Teachers: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will review eligibility arrangements for the teacher's Pension Scheme to enable supply teachers to participate in that scheme.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","29634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457506","Department for Education","false","2016-03-08","<p>On Monday 7 March the Department published our consultation for a national funding formula, which is now open until 17 April. The consultation explains our proposals to use an area cost adjustment to reflect variation in labour market costs, given the significant impact of such costs to school spending. We are currently consulting on which methodology we should use to do this, and will bring forward our response in due course, once the consultation has closed.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-03-08T13:32:14.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457506/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457506/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457506/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-03","Schools: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the additional (a) salary and (b) other costs which are incurred by schools in London, compared with those outside London; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","29640"
