"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458725","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-09","<p>Taxpayers money should not be diverted away from its intended purpose and wasted on political campaigning and political lobbying. The clause does not stop grant recipients, including charities, from using other sources of funding for this or from making their views known.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","903988 ; 903990","2016-03-09T14:45:25.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458725/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458725/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458725/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-03-03","Charities: Lobbying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what representations he has received from charities on the Government's proposal to prevent charities using government grants to lobby Parliament.","false","Biography information for Colleen Fletcher","Coventry North East","Colleen Fletcher","903987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458726","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-09","<p>The UK is recognised as the world leader in social investment.</p><p>Across the country, social investment is helping social enterprises tackle issues and transform lives. It has an important role in building a more sustainable, resilient social sector.</p><p>We have created funds and programmes, which support these organisations to access investment and increase their impact.</p><p>I want this leadership to continue, and this Government is absolutely committed to growing this essential marketplace.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-03-09T14:26:58.66Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458726/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458726/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458726/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-03-03","Social Enterprises: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what progress his Department has made on developing social finance.","false","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","903992"
