"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456849","The Lord Chairman of Committees","false","2016-03-14","<p>815 members are not on leave of absence or disqualified as members of the judiciary; 30 have taken leave of absence; 8 are disqualified as members of the judiciary.</p><p>You may find it helpful to know that up-to-date information about membership of the House is available on the Parliamentary website: <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/mps-lords-and-offices/lords/composition-of-the-lords/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/mps-lords-and-offices/lords/composition-of-the-lords/</a>.</p>",,"Lord Laming",,"2016-03-14T14:42:06.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456849/answer","Biography information for Lord Laming","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456849/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456849/answer",,,,,"200",,"Chairman of Committees (HoL)","2016-03-02","Peers","2","House of Lords","To ask the Chairman of Committees what is the current number of Members of the House (1) not on leave of absence, and (2) on leave of absence.","false","Biography information for Lord Foulkes of Cumnock",,"Lord Foulkes of Cumnock","HL6663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456850","The Lord Chairman of Committees","false","2016-03-14","<p>There are nine members who are currently eligible to attend the House but have yet to attend in the 2015/16 Session. They are:</p><p> </p><p>L. Alliance</p><p>L. Bridges</p><p>L. Cameron of Lochbroom</p><p>B. Hanham</p><p>L. Inge</p><p>L. Neill of Bladen</p><p>L. Thomas of Macclesfield</p><p>B. Thomas of Walliswood</p><p>L. Wade of Chorlton</p><p> </p><p>This list does not include members who are on leave of absence or who are disqualified from attending as members of the judiciary.</p>",,"Lord Laming",,"2016-03-14T14:01:11.793Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456850/answer","Biography information for Lord Laming","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456850/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456850/answer",,,,,"200",,"Chairman of Committees (HoL)","2016-03-02","Peers: Attendance","2","House of Lords","To ask the Chairman of Committees which Members of the House have so far attended no sittings of the House this Session.","false","Biography information for Lord Foulkes of Cumnock",,"Lord Foulkes of Cumnock","HL6664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456851","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-15","<p>The Government remains committed to developing the UK as a global centre for Islamic Finance. This work includes issuing sovereign Sukuk of £200 million in 2014; adapting the tax regime to remove the major tax barriers to Islamic finance transactions; and UK Export Finance issuing its first ever Sharia-compliant export credit guarantee for a 10-year US$913 million Sukuk that was issued by Emirates Airlines in March 2015. This was used to finance the acquisition of 4 Airbus A380 aircraft.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-03-15T16:26:11.423Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456851/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456851/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456851/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-02","Financial Services: Islam","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will provide an update on their policy on Islamic finance in the UK.","false","Biography information for Lord Greaves",,"Lord Greaves","HL6665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456852","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-15","<p>The Government has not made any submissions to the Bank of England's consultation: Establishing Shari'ah compliant central bank liquidity facilities.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-03-15T16:25:04.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456852/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456852/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456852/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-02","Financial Services: Islam","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what submissions they have made to the Bank of England's consultation <i>Establishing Shari'ah compliant central bank liquidity facilities</i>.","false","Biography information for Lord Greaves",,"Lord Greaves","HL6666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456853","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-15","<p>The Bank of England will decide whether or not to establish a Shari’ah compliant liquidity facility in light of feedback to its consultation from the market and other relevant stakeholders. None of the proposals in the consultation are expected to require a change to primary legislation. Once the Bank of England has concluded, the Government will consider whether there is a need for Parliament to review legislation in relation to Islamic Finance in the UK more widely.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-03-15T16:25:31.523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456853/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456853/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456853/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-02","Financial Services: Islam","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether Parliament will be involved in the scrutiny of any proposals for changes to systems of Islamic finance in the UK following the outcome of the Bank of England's consultation.","false","Biography information for Lord Greaves",,"Lord Greaves","HL6667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456854","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>The new clause will not prevent recipients from performing activities that are part of the intended purpose of the grant. It makes sure that taxpayers’ money is not diverted from their intended purpose and wasted on political campaigning and political lobbying. <br>As indicated at the House of Lords Science Technology Committee, BIS and Cabinet Office are looking into how this new clause will apply to academic research.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","HL6669 ; HL6670","2016-04-18T16:37:03.783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456854/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456854/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456854/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-03-02","Lobbying","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the new Cabinet Office guidelines that no government grants may be used to lobby for new regulation or more government funding would preclude academics at publicly funded universities, or charities in receipt of grants for specific work, from giving evidence to parliamentary select committees drawing on such publicly funded research.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town",,"Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town","HL6668"
