"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456857","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-15","<p>The measure of the structural deficit that excludes capital is the ‘Cyclically-adjusted current budget’ (CACB). According to the Office for Budget Responsibility’s November 2015 ‘Economic and fiscal outlook’, the CACB is forecast to reach a surplus by 2017-18 of 0.5 per cent of GDP.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2016-03-15T16:27:05.73Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456857/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456857/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456857/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-02","Public Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they expect to have balanced the structural deficit excluding capital expenditure.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kramer",,"Baroness Kramer","HL6671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456858","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-16","<p>In carrying out government business, Ministers, officials and special advisers must abide by their respective Codes of Conduct.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-03-16T17:28:35.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456858/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456858/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456858/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-03-02","Government Departments: Newspaper Press","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether any (1) minister, (2) official, or (3) ministerial special adviser, have played any part in the drafting of letters subsequently signed by retired military officers or business people and published in national newspapers in the last year.","false","Biography information for Lord Tebbit",,"Lord Tebbit","HL6672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456859","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-14","<p>I refer the Noble Lord to the Prime Minister's oral response to the Hon Member for Mid Bedfordshire on 22 February 2016: Column 32.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-03-14T12:33:34.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456859/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456859/answer","HL6673 attachment.pdf","Attachment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456859/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-03-02","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether any (1) minister, (2) official, or (3) ministerial special adviser, importuned any persons to sign letters concerning the European Referendum or the consequences of a national vote for leaving the EU in national newspapers; and if so, (a) how many were importuned, (b) how many signed, and (c) how many declined to do so.","false","Biography information for Lord Tebbit",,"Lord Tebbit","HL6673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456916","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-10","<p>The Department will shortly be publishing an Equality Impact Assessment on the proposal to close the office at St Paul’s Place, Sheffield, which will include an assessment of the diversity implications.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-03-10T16:43:38.34Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456916/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456916/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456916/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-02","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will publish the impact assessment carried out by his Department's board on the closure of St Paul's Place, Sheffield; and what account his Department took of the diversity implications of that closure.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","29371"
