"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457105","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-09","<p>In 2014-15 HM Courts &amp;Tribunals Service reviewed outstanding cases in employment tribunals and removed a backlog of very old cases which had settled or were completed from the case management system. The overall trend in average clearance time for single cases continues to improve and this can be seen in the Published Statistics at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/tribunals-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/tribunals-statistics</a>.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-03-09T15:30:24.333Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457105/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457105/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457105/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-02","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 11 February 2016 to Question 25609, what assessment he has made of the reasons for the increase in the average time taken for national minimum wage cases in employment tribunals between 2013-14 and 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","29476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457106","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-08","<p>Further reforms were announced in the Chancellor’s Autumn Statement in November. Those reforms will remove the right to compensation for pain, suffering and loss of amenity from minor whiplash injuries, and reduce legal costs by raising the small claims limit for personal injury claims to £5,000. The government will consult on the detail of these reforms in due course, with a view to implementing them as soon as the necessary legislation is in place.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2016-03-08T17:09:44.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457106/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457106/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457106/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-02","Personal Injury: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what progress his Department has made on implementing the recommendations of the whiplash reform programme.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","29487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457107","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-07","<p>This information is not held by the Ministry of Justice.</p><p>The Disclosure and Barring Service are responsible for managing and processing criminal record checks.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-03-07T15:53:28.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457107/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457107/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457107/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-02","Criminal Records: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people aged (a) 14 to 17 and (b) 18 to 21 have a criminal record in England.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","29555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457108","Department of Health","false","2016-03-07","<p>No representations have been made to the Department in respect of the retoxification of prisoners with a history of drug addiction prior to their release.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-03-07T15:37:29.863Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457108/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457108/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457108/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-02","Prisoners' Release: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what representations his Department has received on the practice of retoxification prior to their release of prisoners who have a history of drug addictions.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","29577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457109","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-09","<p>The decision as to whether the EU-Canada Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement and the EU-US Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership will be mixed agreements will be taken by the EU and its Member States when each agreement is signed.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-03-09T14:26:21.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457109/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457109/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457109/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-02","Trade Agreements: North America","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, who will take the decision on whether (a) the EU-Canada Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement and (b) the EU-US Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership are agreements requiring ratification by Parliament; and when such a decision will be taken.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","29514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457110","Scotland Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>I refer the hon Gentleman to my answer of 4 March 2016.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","29583","2016-03-07T11:25:08.157Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457110/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457110/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/457110/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-03-02","Economic Situation: Dundee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, with reference to the Joseph Rowntree Foundation report, Uneven Growth: Tackling City Decline, published in February 2016, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the findings of that report in Dundee.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","29582"
