f the six clinical priority areas in the CCG IAF that will be overseen by an independent group.</p><p> </p><p>The CCG IAF proposals are subject to the outcome of an engagement process which closed for comments on February 26 2016. More information can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/ccg-improvmnt/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/ccg-improvmnt/</a></p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL6583 ; HL6586","2016-03-14T15:15:43.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456351/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456351/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456351/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-01","Diabetes: Health Education","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much money the NHS invested in ensuring access to and provision of structured education for diabetes patients in (1) 2013, (2) 2014 and (3) 2015, and what percentage those figures represent of total NHS spend on diabetes during each year.","false","Biography information for Lord Harrison",,"Lord Harrison","HL6585"
