"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456388","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-21","<p>The information requested on applications to Russell Group Higher Education Institutions (HEIs) by socio-economic group is not held by government.</p><p> </p><p>The Higher Education Statistics Agency (HESA) collects and publishes information on students entering and qualifying from UK HEIs. A breakdown of this information for each National Statistics Socio-economic Classification (NS-SEC) grouping is not published and could only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Provider-level statistics on the share of students from disadvantaged backgrounds are published as part of HESA’s <em>UK Performance Indicators,</em> and these include data on the proportion of young full-time first degree entrants who fall under NS-SEC categories 4 to 7. The data is provided in the table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="6"><p>Percentage of UK-domiciled young full-time first degree entrants from NS-SEC categories 4 to 7 (1)</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>English Higher Education Institutions</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>Academic Years 2005/06 to 2014/15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Academic Year</p></td><td><p>2005/06 (2)</p></td><td><p>2006/07</p></td><td><p>2007/08</p></td><td><p>2008/09 (3)</p></td><td><p>2009/10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All Russell Group HEIs in England (2)</p></td><td><p>19.3%</p></td><td><p>19.0%</p></td><td><p>19.1%</p></td><td><p>N/A</p></td><td><p>18.5%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All English HEIs</p></td><td><p>29.1%</p></td><td><p>29.8%</p></td><td><p>29.4%</p></td><td><p>N/A</p></td><td><p>30.1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Academic Year</p></td><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>2014/15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All Russell Group HEIs in England (2)</p></td><td><p>18.8%</p></td><td><p>18.3%</p></td><td><p>19.7%</p></td><td><p>20.0%</p></td><td><p>20.2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All English HEIs</p></td><td><p>30.7%</p></td><td><p>30.9%</p></td><td><p>32.8%</p></td><td><p>33.1%</p></td><td><p>33.1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Source: HESA Performance Indicators</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Notes:</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>(1) Groups 4 to 7 of the NS-SEC include small employers, own account workers, and lower supervisory, technical , semi-routine and routine occupations</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>(2) The Russell Group HEIs included are all those that were part of the Russell Group on March 8<sup>th</sup> 2016</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>(3) Data for 2005/06 excludes the University of Cambridge due to a change in its data recording for that academic year</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="6"><p>(4) The change in UCAS question for 2008/09 applicants had an impact on the NS-SEC indicators, making them incomparable with data published prior to and post 2008/09</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Prime Minister announced in January 2016 that the Government intends to legislate to require individual universities to publish statistical information on admissions by gender, class and ethnic background in order to make each institution’s record on admissions more transparent.</p>",,"Baroness Evans of Bowes Park",,"2016-03-21T14:06:13.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456388/answer","Biography information for Baroness Evans of Bowes Park","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456388/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456388/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-01","Graduates","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of graduates from Russell Group universities in each year for the past 10 years came from each socio-economic group.","false","Biography information for Lord Livermore",,"Lord Livermore","HL6617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456389","Department for Education","false","2016-03-14","<p>The information requested is not collected by the Department.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-03-14T12:31:29.693Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456389/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456389/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456389/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-01","GCE A-level","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of pupils in each socio-economic group achieved three grade A* to B at A Level in each year for the past 10 years.","false","Biography information for Lord Livermore",,"Lord Livermore","HL6618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456390","Department of Health","false","2016-03-10","<p>No comparison has been made between the NHS Drug Tariff reimbursement price for England and Wales and the price of coal tar preparations produced by National Health Service hospital manufacturers. Any comparison would need to be treated with caution as some hospitals’ prices will not include the same overhead costs as commercial suppliers, nor might they have the infrastructure needed to supply to any pharmacy or indeed all pharmacies.</p><p> </p><p>A comparison of the reimbursement prices of specials listed on the Scottish Drug Tariff with those on the English Drug Tariff in Autumn 2015 showed there were 40 products listed on both Tariffs that were the same or similar. Out of these, 50% were more expensive on the Scottish Drug Tariff in comparison with the English Drug Tariff. The products are not necessarily exactly the same and the reimbursement arrangements in Scotland operate in different ways to those in England.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-03-10T13:40:16.06Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456390/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456390/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456390/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-01","NHS: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of how the price of 100 grams of five per cent coal tar ointment on the NHS Drugs Tariff for England and Wales compares with (1) the price of that treatment from manufacturing pharmacies, and (2) the price of that treatment on the Scottish NHS Drugs Tariff; and whether they will provide those figures.","false","Biography information for Baroness Masham of Ilton",,"Baroness Masham of Ilton","HL6619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456391","Department of Health","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Health and Social Care Information Centre collects data on the number of staff working in National Health Service hospital and community health services in England.</p><p>Nationality is a self-reported field within the NHS electronic staff record system. Of those individuals who declared their nationality, 1,050,034 (93.5%) are European Union nationals (this includes 994,693 British nationals and 55,341 other EU nationals). There are a further 73,681 (6.5%) non United Kingdom and non EU nationals.</p><p><em> </em></p><p><br></p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL6621","2016-03-14T15:13:16.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456391/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456391/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456391/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-01","NHS: Migrant Workers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many EU nationals work in the NHS in England.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL6620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456392","Department of Health","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Health and Social Care Information Centre collects data on the number of staff working in National Health Service hospital and community health services in England.</p><p>Nationality is a self-reported field within the NHS electronic staff record system. Of those individuals who declared their nationality, 1,050,034 (93.5%) are European Union nationals (this includes 994,693 British nationals and 55,341 other EU nationals). There are a further 73,681 (6.5%) non United Kingdom and non EU nationals.</p><p><em> </em></p><p><br></p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL6620","2016-03-14T15:13:16.883Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456392/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456392/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456392/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-01","NHS: Migrant Workers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many non-UK, non-EU nationals work in the NHS in England.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL6621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456394","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-08","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-03-08T16:44:49.043Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456394/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456394/answer","HL6622 FINAL.pdf","Referral Letter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456394/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-03-01","Childbirth","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many live births there were in 2015 at 23 and 24 weeks gestation.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL6622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456395","Department of Health","false","2016-03-14","<p>This data is not currently available. Abortion data for 2015 will be published by the Department in May.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-03-14T15:28:07.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456395/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456395/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456395/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-01","Abortion","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many abortions there were in 2015 at 23 weeks gestation and above.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL6623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456396","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-09","<p>The latest figures for the UK’s balance of trade with the EU are publically available in the ONS Balance of Payments: Quarter 3 (July to Sept) 2015 publication.</p><p>The UK’s balance of trade in goods &amp; services with the EU in 2014 was -£58.8 billion, relating to £230.2 billion in exports and £289.1 billion in imports.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Maude of Horsham",,"2016-03-09T16:36:08.14Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456396/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456396/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456396/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-01","UK Trade with EU","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what are the latest figures for the UK's balance of trade with the EU.","false","Biography information for Lord Hoyle",,"Lord Hoyle","HL6624"
